00:59:42,400 --> 00:59:47,599
Lewis problem and Day Park's problem and the problem of the external world and the problem of other minds.

652
00:59:47,599 --> 00:59:58,720
No, Heidegger knows that we're in the world, but we're always in the world from sort of a point of view, a perspective.

