01:00:11,000 --> 01:00:22,760
I mean, he says Dasein is being in the world, Heidegger, and he says, I've got a line I quote from way back on 414, whatever it is, Dasein is its world existingly.

657
01:00:22,759 --> 01:00:25,400
And what he's got is now he's got that problem.

658
01:00:25,400 --> 01:00:37,240
He's trying to talk about how we are open heads turned toward the world, but from a particular point of view.

659
01:00:37,239 --> 01:00:47,560
And you mustn't hear the point of view as particular like in the Renaissance when they were trying to exactly figure out where the perspective on the world is.

660
01:00:47,560 --> 01:00:50,440
That's getting you too much into subjects.

661
01:00:50,440 --> 01:00:52,119
Think of medieval painting.

662
01:00:52,119 --> 01:00:59,080
Think of Giotto, who painted things as big or little, depending on how meaningful they were.

663
01:00:59,960 --> 01:01:01,399
There was still a point of view.

664
01:01:02,279 --> 01:01:11,639
